  -- notes_en
  E'BIRTH DATE: December 30, 1952, Goiás. Confirmed exact from multiple sources.

NAME: Julival do Espírito Santo. Sometimes spelled "Julival do Espíritu Santo" in sources.

APELIDO CONTEXT: Uses "Silvestre" to distinguish from:
- Mestre Gato (Fernando Albuquerque) - Grupo Senzala founder, Rio de Janeiro
- Mestre Gato Preto (José Gabriel Goés/Geronimo Souza Góes) - Bahia Angola master

TEACHERS:
- Mestre Onça Tigre (Milton Freire de Carvalho) - uncle; first introduction to capoeira in Goiás
- Cláudio Danadinho - Brasília; Senzala co-founder, student of Mestre Arraia (Pastinha lineage)
- Mestre Silvestre (Silvestre Vitório Ferreira) - São Paulo; primary teacher; awarded mestre title

STUDENTS (First in Manaus):
- Spartacus (Édson Colyer Brás da Silva, 1951-1977) - first student; vale-tudo fighter
- Américo Omena
- Fernando Lopes (police delegate)
- Marcos, Maurício, Almir Dantas (brothers)
- Carrasco Cearense (fighter)
- Magriça, Paulinho, Marcolino Salgado
- Fernando Lemos de Almeida
- Newton Ferreira Filho
- Wallace and José Wilson Cavalcante (brothers)

TIMELINE DISCREPANCY:
Sources consistently say he founded Zumbí dos Palmares academy in "February 1972" but arrived in Manaus in "June 1972" or "second half of 1972". Most likely: he arrived late 1971 or early 1972, with the academy formally founded February 1972.

I ENCONTRO DE CAPOEIRA DA AMAZÔNIA:
Occurred "late 1970s" - exact year not specified. Mestre Silvestre traveled to Manaus for this event and awarded Gato his mestre diploma there.

